snippet.textDisplay: Hats off salute to Pritam Hasan vai... the way you bring the assence of rural beuaty of bangladesh in the form of music is outstanding.. the theme of coke studio bangla should be it.. amazing... People are saying chad pitano song(roof slappers song)..its actually not.... These women are construction workers we say in bengali JUWALI..They usually sing music while they are being tired of work and normally they sing unique and ethnic bengali folkstories in the form of a chorus, because it boosts up their energy level  and it helps maintaining the same pace , rythm of work.. Here they were singing Behula Lakhindar stories in the form of a chorus, Specially labourers while they also cut paddies or any corps in the field they sing this music in a chorus...at least 50/60 people sing this chorus music in the field.....This music represents BANGLADESH, the People OF Bangladesh.....Amazing Pritam bhai you have understoood what coke studio listeners are waiting for.
